How to play!

First, make a directory somewhere named "/lair" or something. Then you
NEED to ASSIGN this directory to "Lair:". PUT ALL FILES IN THE LAIR
DIRECTORY! Then to run it, cd to "Lair:" and type "lair" or "run lair"
and if all the correct files are in the directory UNALTERED the game
should run fine!

	You then will be asked for 1 or 2 players. If its just you, just
type "1" and then the game will continue on. The game is pretty self
explanitory from there.

Playing with another person via modem!

This DOES work, I have tested it with another person a lot. The only 
thing is the process of getting to do it. Select 2 players when you run,
you will then be asked for the baud you wish to set the modem port at. 
After that you will be put into a terminal mode. When you see the person
call by the result "RING" coming to your screen, type "ATA". Then the
two of you can talk freely. If it doesnt show what you type, or if it
echos everything funny, you have to set your modem with ATE command.. 
When you two are ready, you have to hit CTRL-P and it will let you play.
Everything from there is pretty self explanitory. 

BUGS! ? 

This is version 1.0.. This game is NOT by any means CLOSE to completetion. 
What it basically is, is a rough skeleton for the finished product. There
are 61 rooms total in this version. Explore all you wish. Fight the 
monsters you encounter, help each other out. Collect objects. There isnt
a set adventure or objective yet, mainly because I havent coded it all
yet. I want people to try this game out and to let me know wht bugs they
find and what they think should be added, or changed. My final goal is to
finish this game with over 500 rooms, a full adventure, and mini mysteries
to be solved. Puzzles to be solved, etc. But before I code all of that I
just want to know what you feel about it. This version IS fairly stable
as far as I can tell after playing it often. Happy gaming!


